[{"id":"VR860285","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">What is the magnitude of the force exerted by the electric field on the test charge at the position shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mn>2</mn> </math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR860285_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A parallel-plate capacitor is charged so that a uniform electric field with magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"E\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"E\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mi>E</mi> </math></span></span> is created between the plates. A test charge with charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive q\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"positive q\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi></math></span></span> is placed halfway between the plates, as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>. The force exerted on the test charge by the electric field has magnitude <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"F\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>F</mi></math></span></span>. The test charge is then moved half the distance to the negatively charged plate, as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>.</p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a capacitor with two parallel plates and a test charge between the plates in two different positions, labeled Figure 1 and Figure 2. The parallel plates of the capacitor are horizontal with the lower plate positively charged and the upper plate negatively charged. Figure 1 shows a test charge with charge positive q halfway between the plates at a distance d from each plate. Figure 2 shows the same test charge with charge positive q in a higher position between the two plates at a distance of d over 2 from the upper negatively charged plate and a distance of 3 d over 2 from the lower positively charged plate. A note states that the figures are not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR860285.g01.svg\" /></div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F over 2\"><math alttext=\"F over 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>F</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F\"><math alttext=\"F\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>F</mi></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 F\"><math alttext=\"2 F\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>F</mi></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"4 F\"><math alttext=\"4 F\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mi>F</mi></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":1}]